<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="523">Range Hispaniola, recorded from both Haiti and the Dominican Republic, within 800-1600 m. An apparent endemic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="523">biology In Haiti, the type colonies were recorded as nesting in soil (W. M. Mann), while in the Dominican Republic, the Constanza</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="523">colony was found beneath a rock in a pine-hardwood forested ravine (W. L. and D. E. Brown).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
